  "comment_text": {
    "snp1.5:2.3": "<i lang='pi' translate='no'>Sakkhipuṭṭho</i> is only elsewhere used in the context of being asked to bear witness in court. I think the context is relevant here, as the Buddha is offering personal testimony on “judging” others. ",
    "snp1.5:6.2": "Norman and Bodhi both read <i lang='pi' translate='no'>pada</i> as “way”, but it surely means “passage” as eg. <a href='https://suttacentral.net/an4.191/en/sujato#1.7'>AN 4.191:1.7</a>. "
  },
