  "root_text": {
    "snp1.5:0.1": "Sutta Nipāta 1.5 ",
    "snp1.5:0.2": "Cundasutta ",
    "snp1.5:1.1": "“Pucchāmi muniṁ pahūtapaññaṁ, ",
    "snp1.5:1.2": "(iti cundo kammāraputto) ",
    "snp1.5:1.3": "Buddhaṁ dhammassāmiṁ vītataṇhaṁ; ",
    "snp1.5:1.4": "Dvipaduttamaṁ sārathīnaṁ pavaraṁ, ",
    "snp1.5:1.5": "Kati loke samaṇā tadiṅgha brūhi”. ",
    "snp1.5:2.1": "“Caturo samaṇā na pañcamatthi, ",
    "snp1.5:2.2": "(cundāti bhagavā) ",
    "snp1.5:2.3": "Te te āvikaromi sakkhipuṭṭho; ",
    "snp1.5:2.4": "Maggajino maggadesako ca, ",
    "snp1.5:2.5": "Magge jīvati yo ca maggadūsī”. ",
    "snp1.5:3.1": "“Kaṁ maggajinaṁ vadanti buddhā, ",
    "snp1.5:3.2": "(iti cundo kammāraputto) ",
    "snp1.5:3.3": "Maggakkhāyī kathaṁ atulyo hoti; ",
    "snp1.5:3.4": "Magge jīvati me brūhi puṭṭho, ",
    "snp1.5:3.5": "Atha me āvikarohi maggadūsiṁ”. ",
    "snp1.5:4.1": "“Yo tiṇṇakathaṅkatho visallo, ",
    "snp1.5:4.2": "Nibbānābhirato anānugiddho; ",
    "snp1.5:4.3": "Lokassa sadevakassa netā, ",
    "snp1.5:4.4": "Tādiṁ maggajinaṁ vadanti buddhā. ",
    "snp1.5:5.1": "Paramaṁ paramanti yodha ñatvā, ",
    "snp1.5:5.2": "Akkhāti vibhajate idheva dhammaṁ; ",
    "snp1.5:5.3": "Taṁ kaṅkhachidaṁ muniṁ anejaṁ, ",
    "snp1.5:5.4": "Dutiyaṁ bhikkhunamāhu maggadesiṁ. ",
    "snp1.5:6.1": "Yo dhammapade sudesite, ",
    "snp1.5:6.2": "Magge jīvati saññato satīmā; ",
    "snp1.5:6.3": "Anavajjapadāni sevamāno, ",
    "snp1.5:6.4": "Tatiyaṁ bhikkhunamāhu maggajīviṁ. ",
    "snp1.5:7.1": "Chadanaṁ katvāna subbatānaṁ, ",
    "snp1.5:7.2": "Pakkhandī kuladūsako pagabbho; ",
    "snp1.5:7.3": "Māyāvī asaññato palāpo, ",
    "snp1.5:7.4": "Patirūpena caraṁ sa maggadūsī. ",
    "snp1.5:8.1": "Ete ca paṭivijjhi yo gahaṭṭho, ",
    "snp1.5:8.2": "Sutavā ariyasāvako sapañño; ",
    "snp1.5:8.3": "Sabbe netādisāti ñatvā, ",
    "snp1.5:8.4": "Iti disvā na hāpeti tassa saddhā; ",
    "snp1.5:8.5": "Kathaṁ hi duṭṭhena asampaduṭṭhaṁ, ",
    "snp1.5:8.6": "Suddhaṁ asuddhena samaṁ kareyyā”ti. ",
    "snp1.5:8.7": "Cundasuttaṁ pañcamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "snp1.5:0.1": "Anthology of Discourses 1.5 ",
    "snp1.5:0.2": "With Cunda ",
    "snp1.5:1.1": "“I ask the sage abounding in wisdom,” ",
    "snp1.5:1.2": "said Cunda the smith, ",
    "snp1.5:1.3": "“the Buddha, master of the teaching, free of craving, ",
    "snp1.5:1.4": "best of men, excellent charioteer, please tell me this: ",
    "snp1.5:1.5": "how many ascetics are there in the world?” ",
    "snp1.5:2.1": "“There are four ascetics, not a fifth.” ",
    "snp1.5:2.2": "said the Buddha to Cunda, ",
    "snp1.5:2.3": "“Being asked to bear witness, <j>I will explain them to you: ",
    "snp1.5:2.4": "the path-victor, the path-teacher, ",
    "snp1.5:2.5": "the path-liver, and the path-wrecker.” ",
    "snp1.5:3.1": "“Who is a path-victor according to the Buddhas?” ",
    "snp1.5:3.2": "said Cunda the smith, ",
    "snp1.5:3.3": "“and how is one an unequaled explainer of the path? ",
    "snp1.5:3.4": "Tell me when asked about one who lives the path, ",
    "snp1.5:3.5": "then declare the path-wrecker.” ",
    "snp1.5:4.1": "“Rid of indecision, free of thorns, ",
    "snp1.5:4.2": "delighting in extinguishment, not fawning, ",
    "snp1.5:4.3": "a guide for the world with its gods. ",
    "snp1.5:4.4": "The Buddhas say one such is victor of the path. ",
    "snp1.5:5.1": "Knowing the ultimate as ultimate, ",
    "snp1.5:5.2": "they explain and analyze the teaching right here. ",
    "snp1.5:5.3": "That sage unstirred, with doubt cut off, ",
    "snp1.5:5.4": "is the second mendicant, I say, the teacher of the path. ",
    "snp1.5:6.1": "Living restrained and mindful on the path ",
    "snp1.5:6.2": "of the well-taught passage of teaching, ",
    "snp1.5:6.3": "cultivating blameless states, ",
    "snp1.5:6.4": "is the third mendicant, I say, the path-liver. ",
    "snp1.5:7.1": "Dressed like one true to their vows, ",
    "snp1.5:7.2": "pushy, rude, a corrupter of families, ",
    "snp1.5:7.3": "devious, unrestrained, chaff, ",
    "snp1.5:7.4": "the path-wrecker’s life is a sham. ",
    "snp1.5:8.1": "A layperson who gets this, ",
    "snp1.5:8.2": "a learned, wise noble disciple, ",
    "snp1.5:8.3": "knows that ‘They are not all like that one’. ",
    "snp1.5:8.4": "So when they see them they don’t lose their faith. ",
    "snp1.5:8.5": "For how could one equate them—",
    "snp1.5:8.6": "the corrupt with the uncorrupt, <j>the pure with the impure?” "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "snp1.5:1.4": "Dvipaduttamaṁ → dipaduttamaṁ (bj, sya-all, km, pts-vp-pli1) ",
